cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is about tabling, which is a well-known extension of Prolog used in logic programming. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the implementation of tabling, which involves control flow and optimization, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the practicality and performance of tabling, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a lightweight approach to tabling, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
